<subSubSection lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,1188,2043]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1584,1610]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Description.</emphasis>
Based on all specimens examined. Preserved specimens pale or reddish in colour, conical in shape (
<figureCitation box="[160,297,1620,1646]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18A–B</figureCitation>
). Body length 17.0–53.0 mm including paleae and scaphe, width 4.7–9.0 mm at cephalic regions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,1188,2043]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Cephalic veil semicircular, free from operculum, with 26–32 smooth cirri on anterior and lateral margins (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18C–D</figureCitation>
). Pair of ear-shaped lobes adjacent to both sides of dorsal base of cephalic veil. Buccal tentacles with deep median longitudinal grooves, arising posterior to cephalic veil from buccal cavity, extending over margin of cephalic veil (
<figureCitation box="[284,422,1764,1790]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,1188,2043]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Operculum semicircular; dorsal and lateral margins well developed, smooth; ventral margin (opercular ridge) with 11–12 pairs of acute and golden paleae, curved dorsally, with extended tips (
<figureCitation box="[1064,1198,1836,1863]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18C, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,1188,2043]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Segments 1–2 with pair of tentacular cirri respectively, annulate, tapering to tip (
<figureCitation box="[1106,1240,1872,1898]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18C–E</figureCitation>
). Segment 2 with complete and smooth dorsal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[533,666,1908,1935]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18C, E</figureCitation>
). Segments 3–4 with pair of lateral comb-like branchiae respectively, with dorso-lateral pad adjacent to branchia (
<figureCitation box="[644,782,1944,1970]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18C–D</figureCitation>
). Distinct ventral glandular lobes present on segments 3–6 (
<figureCitation box="[160,265,1980,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Segment 4 with pair of lateral humps near branchiae (
<figureCitation box="[905,1011,1980,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Segment 20 with a complete dorsal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[215,348,2016,2043]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18G, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Notopodia other than those of segment 1 which bear paleae, on segments 5–20 (16 pairs), each bearing 
<specimenCount pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
of capillaries. Neuropodia, 13 pairs on segments 8–20, each with raised torus with a transverse row of uncini; each uncinus with U-shaped anterior peg embedded into torus, several rows of minor teeth, two longitudinal rows of major teeth, each with about seven teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Scaphe distinctly separated from segment 21 (
<figureCitation box="[731,872,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18G–H</figureCitation>
). Scaphe longer than broad, arched ventrally and flattened dorsally with crenulated lateral margin. Anal flap tongue-shaped with tip, with crenulated margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18H–I</figureCitation>
). Scaphal hooks 4–7 pairs, short, barely visible, with a curved blunt tip (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1142,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@34.[174,1414,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pectinaria torquata Zhang &amp; Qiu, 2017 Methyl Green stained body (SCSMBC030933): A. Ventral view of entire body; B. Lateral view of entire body; C. Lateral view of anterior end; D. Ventral view of anterior end; E. Dorso-lateral view of anterior end; F. Lateral view of posterior end; G. Dorsal view of posterior end; H. Ventral view of posterior end; I. Anal flap. Abbreviations: af, anal flap; br, branchiae; bt, buccal tentacles; cv, cephalic veil; dl, dorsal lobe; dlp, dorso-lateral pad; lh, lateral hump; nep, neuropodium; op, operculum; or, opercular rim; p, paleae; s, segment; sc, scaphe; sh, scaphal hooks; tc, tentacular cirri; vl, ventral lappet." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
